               <head>Tazkirat al-salatin-i Chaghata, volume 2</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Taz̲irat al-salāṭīn-i Chaghatā by Muḥammad Hādī Kāmvar Khān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85135483 http://lccn.loc.gov/n83158321" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3918-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658595.0x000001 viaf_65267429">Muḥammad Hādī Kāmvar Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658595.0x000001 viaf_65267429" type="supplied">محمّد هادى كامور خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9535">Taz̲irat al-salāṭīn-i Chaghatā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_9535">تذكرۃ السّلاطين چغتا</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>
                           <term xml:lang="en">History</term> of the <term xml:lang="en">Timurid</term> Dynasty, especially its '<term xml:lang="en">Mughal</term>' descendants in <term xml:lang="en">South Asia</term>, begun under <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Muḥammad Shāh</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Consists of the second volume only, continued until <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">Jumādá I 1136</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1724</date>, equating to month 2 of <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ilāhī</term> year 6 of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Muḥammad Shāh</persName>'s reign
                        </p>
                        <p>Preceded at the beginning (ff i-vi) by notes by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_8170991" role="ann">William Irvine</persName>, setting out in detail the author's career and biography.
                        </p>
                        <p>Followed by a continuation copied in transliteration from a manuscript in the Library of the Royal Asiatic Society (ff 19); and thereafter by 27 folios of notes, genealogies etc in Irvine's hand.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
